overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a comprehensive specification and SOW. My analysis revealed that
  while core functionalities like the interactive questionnaire, database
  storage, PDF report generation, and admin dashboard were in place, several
  critical features were missing or incomplete. Key gaps included the absence of
  a 1-10 tiredness severity scale with safety messaging, explicit COMISA
  detection, outbound links in the report, and weighted scoring for Excessive
  Daytime Sleepiness (EDS). I developed a detailed plan to address these issues,
  prioritizing them based on impact. I have started implementing the plan by
  successfully integrating the tiredness severity scale into the
   component, updating the associated types and validation,
  and adding the required safety warnings for high severity scores.
